    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks for the reply @vvo. Sorry it has taken me a while to get back to you.\n\nMy issue isn't with the back and forward buttons but if you refresh the page, it doesn't load the current page but loads the first page of results. I uploaded a video of it [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2ctWQhP1Sp4](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2ctWQhP1Sp4)\n\nIt works as expected if you comment this out in `search.js`, then go to the second results page and refresh it loads the correct page.\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.numericSelector({\n    container: '#guests',\n    attributeName: 'person_capacity',\n    operator: '>=',\n    options: [\n      { label: '1 guest', value: 1},\n      { label: '2 guests', value: 2},\n      { label: '3 guests', value: 3},\n      { label: '4 guests', value: 4},\n      { label: '5 guests', value: 5},\n      { label: '6 guests', value: 6}\n    ]\n  })\n);\n```\n",
    "created_at": "2016-09-13T13:00:06Z",
